{
  "texts": [
    "These features show the probability of developing LLMs into educational software or platforms for speaking practice, especially for EFL learners who find it difficult to access experienced person instructors.",
    "In addition, to assist English writing, LLMs can answer questions, generate useful suggestions, and detect surface errors quickly, which means it can be an assistant to promote instructor's work efficiency.However, although most of these studies have a positive result, there are many limitations.",
    "The research gaps of these studies include inadequate linguistic diversity and age diversity of participants, the lack of investigating the differences between middle school students and college students, and a lack of analysis of other LLMs's abilities besides ChatGPT.",
    "This research provides a reference for future research directions.",
    "To advance further, it is recommended to increase the samples' diversity, investigate diverse methods to assist EFL learners of various ages or English levels, and explore different LLMs' capabilities, so that educators can maximize LLMs' advantage and develop teaching strategies suitable for multiple students.While this review provides a comprehensive analysis of the current literature on integrating LLMs into EFL speaking and writing education, it is important to acknowledge several limitations."
  ]
}